result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Alexandria M Kohegyi was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Violate/Harassment Restraining Order, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.125(7).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superAgency.name: District Attorney
superAgency.notes: For the period of this agreement, the defendant will comply with the following conditions:  Defendant shall successfully complete two (2) years of probation through the DOC.  Def shall be placed on informal probation to the Iron County District Attorney's Office for a period of two (2) years.  The def shall inform the DA's office of change of address within five (5) days.  The defendant shall report quarterly to the Iron County District Attorney's Office in person or by telephone.  The def shall maintain absolute sobriety, have no contact with HH, complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any recommendations.  The defendant agrees to random drug testing upon request by law enforcement.  The def shall pay any applicable attorney fees, court costs and or assessments.  The defendant's bond conditions will not continue.
